com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2

Interface PropagatorFunctionBindings

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, PropagatorFunction
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PropagatorFunctionBindingsImpl

    public interface PropagatorFunctionBindings
extends PropagatorFunction
    A representation of the model object 'PropagatorFunctionBindings'.

    A PropagatorFunctionBindings implements its Bindings logic with the contribution of 2 auxiliary classes

    • The class Bindings, that implements the actual logic as a function of configured dependent model elements. This configuration normally does not change at run time and can be statically set by the concrete PropagatorFunctionBindings. The Bindings instance is provided by the concrete implementation through the method doGetBindings().
    • The class PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings, that is attached to the PropagatorFunctionAdatper of its target EObject. The PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings is a PropagatorFunctionSource, implementing the logic for its owner PropagatorFunction and its target EObject by delegating to its Bindings.

    The PropagatorFunctionBindings implements the derivation of its Antecedents via 2 mechanisms

    • The Antecedents derived from the Bindings and collected via the method PropagatorFunctionSource.collectAntecedents(EList, java.util.function.Predicate)
    • The Antecedents explicitly provided by the concrete implementation by implementing the method doCollectExplicitAntecedents(EList)
    See Also:
    PropagatorPackage.getPropagatorFunctionBindings()
